<TITLE> 1000 to walk free </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com) -- Sheikh Hasina has directed the jail authorities to release a thousand women, children, disabled, sick and long serving prisoners. The prime minister directed the jail authorities to release the 1000 as she formally opened a museum in memory of her father on Saturday. Her spokesman Abul Kalam Azad said she inaugurated two museums at the Dhaka Central Jail: Bangabandhu Prison Memorial Museum or Bangabandhu Kara Smriti Jadugar and Four National Leaders' Prison Memorial Museum. The prime minister placed a wreath at the portrait of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman on the museum premises and prayed for him. The jail authorities renamed the civil cell (Dewani Cell) at the Dhaka Jail as Bangabandhu Prison Memorial Museum. Bangabandhu spent most of his life as political prisoner in that cell. Sheikh Hasina planted a seedling there and watched a presentation titled 'Second Home' (Ditiya Abasan) on the prison life of Bangabandhu. At the Four National Leaders' Museum, she also placed wreath at the portraits of the four-- Syed Nazrul Islam, Tajuddin Ahmed, Mansur Ali and AHM Kamruzzaman who were slain inside the prison on Nov 3, 1975. Deputy leader of the House Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury, home minister Sahara Khatun, finance minister AMA Muhith, agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury were among those present. bdnew
